  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You whisper words of defenestration, as a creature within range is filled with a desire to fly away. Choose one creature you can see within range, it must make a wisdom saving throw:</p><ul><li><strong>Success</strong>: No effect.</li><li><strong>Failure</strong>: On its next turn, the target must use all its movement to get to the highest possible place it can reach on that turn, and throw itself to the ground. If there is no place high enough it can reach that would deal fall damage, the target drops whatever it is holding and falls prone.</li><li><strong>Critical Failure</strong>: As a failure, but the target must also spend its action and bonus action dashing or using the faster route to gain height. If there is no place high enough it can reach that would deal fall damage, it drops whatever it is holding, falls prone, and has its speed reduced to 0 until the end of their next turn.</li></ul><p><strong>At higher ranks:</strong> For each rank above D-rank, increase this jutsu's cost by 3, and the number of affected creatures by +1.</p>",
